simpleText: I understand that comedy shows can be entertaining, and I enjoy them too. However, today's panel discussion left me disheartened. Our culture emphasizes respecting our mothers, but the abusive language used, associating the word 'mother' with private body parts, was unacceptable. While I acknowledge that times are changing, it's essential to maintain respect for our mothers on public platforms. I may face trolling for expressing this, but I implore you to reflect on the impact of such language. Let's uphold India's values of respectfully honoring our mothers and families.   #RespectOurMothers #IndianValues

simpleText: @b1ba593  Yes thats my point as well. That the setup takes a very limited view of depression and its impact which is disappointing cos a lot of the panelists publically present liberal views.
author: @suprateeksinha630

simpleText: @suprateeksinha630  brother, it was a comic set. Obviously, post partum depression is the only one that actually exists is not her viewpoint. She is trying to make a pun about people crying about breakup because now that they have broken up, they won't get pregnant, which in her observation, is much worse. The panelists are aware about worse or atleast depressing situations that are on a similar level, but they don't react to it because it is a stand up set based around her pregnancy experience and the woes of teenage kids breaking up and speaking of depression (probably something to do with celebs taking a 'stand' for depression and then proceed to talk about their breakups and how 'hard it has been').  Anyways, I am sorry. Earlier, I misunderstood your comment thinking that you were stating your opinion that post partum depression is the only legit form of depression. I guess your sarcasm just went whooooshhh above my head 😂😂😂 Sorry again. Have a great day
author: @b1ba593

simpleText: @b1ba593  I get that its a comic set and most of it was witty i admit. Just that we risk trivialising the subject (akin to punching down) when we could aim to broaden the outlook. Your assumption is the audience is knowledgeable to gauge the drift of her point but most of them take it as an opportunity to pile onto a celebrity. Thats where I feel the panel could have made their stand on the topic clear but I guess that would have been a buzzkill. Thanks for your respectful response though 👍
author: @suprateeksinha630

simpleText: @suprateeksinha630  I feel you mate. I think that's probably why Samay did the whole "hum kaise experience kare yeh depression pregnancy ka" part later, as his own way of explaining that this particular logic was flawed. The panelists probably didn't wanna get into the discussion because, let's face it, it's a sensitive topic plus you're up against a woman. High risk, no reward situation. Kudos to samay though, he still went for it.
author: @b1ba593

simpleText: FIRST OF ALL, WHEN DID THE HINDU SCRIPTURES WERE WRITTEN IS NOT KNOWN. ACCORDING TO SWAMI DAYANAND SARASWATI FOUNDER OF ARYA SAMAJ, SCRIPTURES WAS WRITTEN AROUND 1000 MILLION YEARS AGO., AND OTHER SCHOLARS SAYS IT IS 4000, SOME SAY 5000 AND SOME SAY 6000. AND ACCORDING TO SCHOLARS THE VEDAS WERE COMPILED BY VED VYASA.....BUT WE ALSO DON'T KNOW, WHEN HE WAS BORN AND WHEN DID HE COMPILED/WRITTEN THAT....?, THE DATE IS NOT KNOWN ...?. THERE IS ONLY 'SUPPOSED' DATE OF HIS BIRTH I.E 5000 YEAR AGO.. AND WE ALSO DON'T KNOW, IN WHICH PART OF INDIA THE SCRIPTURES WERE REVEALED TO RISHIS ..?..AND WHO WERE THAT RISHIS...?. THE ONLY CLAIMED RISHI IS VED VYASA I.E KRISHNA DVAIPANAYA... NOW, IF YOU DON'T KNOW WHO TRANSFERRED THIS INFORMATION FROM GENERATION TO GENERATION...THEN IT'S LIKE A CHINESE WHISPER; EVERY TIME THE INFORMATION IS PASSED, IT GETS CORRUPTED OR CHANGED .OK. SO EVENTUALLY THERE IS BIG QUESTION MARK ON THE PRESERVATION OF HINDU SCRIPTURES.!. AND IT IS ALSO BELIEVED THAT MANY PART OF VEDAS ARE LOST. AND IT IS ALSO BELIEVED THAT VED VYASA ALSO COMPILED THE PURANAS AND MAHABHARATA. BUT THE PROBLEM IS THAT, THE MAHABHARATA IS ALSO CHANGED TODAY...... EARLIER THERE WAS ONLY FEW THOUSAND SHLOKAS, BUT TODAY THERE ARE 1 LAKH OF IT.
